A dummy_gri is a partial entity definition to be used when types of are constructed. It provides the correct supertypes and the attribute as an empty string.
A dimension_count is a positive integer used to define the coordinate space dimensionality of a .
A dimension_count shall be positive.
The b_spline_curve_form enumerated type is used to indicate that the represents a part of a curve of some specific form.
a connected sequence of line segments represented by degree 1 B-spline basis functions;
an arc of a circle, or a complete circle represented by a B-spline curve;
an arc of ellipse, or a complete ellipse represented by a B-spline curve;
an arc of finite length of a parabola represented by a B-spline curve;
an arc of finite length of an hyperbola represented by a B-spline curve;
a curve for which no particular form is specified;
The b_spline_surface_form enumerated type is used to indicate that the represents a part of a surface of some specific form.
a bounded portion of a plane represented by a B-spline surface of degree 1 in each parameter;
a bounded portion of a cylindrical surface;
a bounded portion of a right circular cone;
a bounded portion of a sphere, or a complete sphere, represented by a B-spline surface;
a torus, or portion of a torus, represented by a B-spline surface;
a bounded portion of a surface of revolution;
a surface constructed from two parametric curves by joining with straight lines corresponding points with the same parameter value on each of the curves.
a special case of a ruled surface in which the second curve degenerates to a single point; when represented by a B-spline surface all the control points along one edge will be coincident;
a bounded portion of one of the class of surfaces of degree 2 in the variables x, y and z;
a bounded portion of a surface of linear extrusion represented by a B-spline surface of degree 1 in one of the parameters;
a surface for which no particular form is specified;
The extent_enumeration type is used to describe the quantitive extent of an object.
the concept of extent is not valid for the quantity being measured;
the extent is zero;
the extent is finite (bounded) but not zero;
the extent is not finite;
The knot_type indicates that the B-spline knots have a particularly simple form enabling the knots themselves to be defaulted;
the form of knots appropriate for a uniform B-spline curve or surface;
the type of knots is not specified; this includes the case of non uniform knots;
the form of knots appropriate for a quasi-uniform B-spline curve or surface;
the form of knots appropriate for a piecewise Bézier curve;
The preferred_surface_curve_representation type is used to indicate the preferred form of representation for a surface curve, which is either a curve in geometric space or in the parametric space of the underlying surfaces;
the curve in three-dimensional space is preferred;
the first pcurve is preferred;
the second pcurve is preferred;
The transition_code type conveys the continuity properties of a composite curve or surface. The continuity referred to is geometric, not parametric continuity.
the segments, or patches, do not join; this is permitted only at the boundary of the curve or surface to indicate that it is not closed.
the segments, or patches, join, but no condition on their tangents is implied;
the segments, or patches, join, and their tangent vectors, or tangent planes, are parallel and have the same direction at the joint; equality of derivatives is not required;
the gradient and curvature are continuous; for a curve, the segments join, their tangent vectors are parallel and in the same direction, and their curvatures are equal at the joint; equality of derivatives is not required; for a surface this implies that the principal curvatures are the same and that the principal directions are coincident along the common boundary.
The trimming_preference type is used to indicate the preferred way of trimming a parametric curve where the trimming is multiply defined.
trimming by cartesian point is preferred;
trimming by parameter value is preferred;;
no trimming preference is communicated;
The axis2_placement select type represents the placing of mutually perpendicular axes in two-dimensional or in three-dimensional Cartesian space.
This select type enables entities requiring axis placement information to reference the axes without specifying the space dimensionality.
